The paper deals with a problem of learning a binary classifier from positive and unlabeled data, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of supervised learning. The paper proposes a novel approach to estimating the class-prior and training a classifier alternately, which involves optimization and statistical inference. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
